gá»“m quáº¿, há»“i, gá»«ng, tháº£o quáº£, Ä‘inh hÆ°Æ¡ng, háº¡t m&ugrave;i... \"B&aacute;nh phá»Ÿ\", theo truyá»�n thá»‘ng, Ä‘Æ°á»£c l&agrave;m tá»« bá»™t gáº¡o, tr&aacute;ng th&agrave;nh táº¥m má»�ng rá»“i cáº¯t th&agrave;nh sá»£i.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cc79d3600b_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Ä�Ä©a rau Ä‘i k&egrave;m phá»Ÿ</em><em>.</em></p>','Wikipedia','','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cc85f10dc6_square.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cc85f10dc6_thumbnail.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cc85f10dc6_small.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cc85f10dc6_crop.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cc85f10dc6_medium.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cc85f10dc6_large.jpg','active',1,'2010-08-31 16:21:44',1,'admin',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'admin','2010-08-31 16:22:05',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'vi_VN'),(27,3,'HÃ¹ng Temple','','hung-temple','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">H&ugrave;ng temple, locating in NghÄ©a LÄ©nh mountain, Cá»• T&iacute;ch village, Hy CÆ°Æ¡ng commune, Phong Ch&acirc;u district, Ph&uacute; Thá»� province, is the most sacred Vietnamese national historic and cultural complex site.</p>','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">H&ugrave;ng temple\'s the place of worship H&ugrave;ng VÆ°Æ¡ng- the first King of Vietnam and the first son of Láº¡c Long Qu&acirc;n and &Acirc;u CÆ¡. H&ugrave;ng temple\'s also the place where was the center of the first capital of Vietnam- Phong Ch&acirc;u, according to ancient tales. It is the symbol of glorious Ä�&ocirc;ng SÆ¡n culture. This temple is the most significant political and social institution of Vietnam. For thousands of year, all Vietnamese dynasties and governments have always regarded it as \"Nam Viá»‡t Triá»‡u Tá»•\" (place of Vietnamese millionth-generation ancestor). All Vietnamese people are proud of it and remember to celebrate Giá»— Tá»• H&ugrave;ng VÆ°Æ¡ng every 10th day of 3rd lunar month here.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Locating</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It told that once upon a time, H&ugrave;ng VÆ°Æ¡ng The First was looking for a place to set up the capital. The King had gone to 99 places but he hadn\'t been satisfactory. One day, he gone to Hy CÆ°Æ¡ng village. Immediately, his horse whinny resoundingly. He stopped and gone to the highest mountain- NghÄ©a LÄ©nh, saw four directions. At last, he decided to choose this place.<br /><br />Ph&uacute; Thá»� is fat and green midland area. In Fengshui opinion, Phong Ch&acirc;u is the land of \"sÆ¡n cháº§u thá»§y tá»¥\" (place where mountains and rivers gather), \"long cháº§u há»• phá»¥c\" (place where dragons and tigers attend upon), \"phÆ°á»£ng bay ngá»±a cháº¡y\" (place where phoenixes fly and horses run) and the land where\'s abundant in \"kh&iacute; thi&ecirc;ng s&ocirc;ng n&uacute;i\" (sacred country\'s qi- flow of energy). This place is full of obstacles and difficult of access that\'s easy to protect, but also easy of access to welcome people come from other places. This is the confluence of 3 rivers: Ä�&agrave; river, red water- Thao river and clear blue water- L&ocirc; river. In front of NghÄ©a LÄ©nh mountain, it\'s Viá»‡t Tr&igrave; three- way crossroads where there\'re tens of turtle- shape low hill direct to H&ugrave;ng temple. Behind NghÄ©a LÄ©nh mountain, it\'s Hy CÆ°Æ¡ng village form a letter- bringing phoenix shape. At the right of this mountain, there\'s Khang Phá»¥ hill like an attending tiger. At the left of this mountain, there\'s An Th&aacute;i hill like an arrow- shooting army general for protecting this temple. At the foot of the mountain, there\'s Cá»• T&iacute;ch village on the horse- shape hill and Tháº­m Th&igrave;nh village where villagers stay awake throung a night to pound rice in order that Lang Li&ecirc;u make b&aacute;nh chÆ°ng and b&aacute;nh d&agrave;y. From Tháº­m Th&igrave;nh to Ph&uacute; Lá»™c, there\'re hills which\'re incarnation of 100 elephants of which 99 elephants direct to H&ugrave;ng temple but 1 elephant didn\'t. That\'s why the God cut off its head and the hill of this elephant still overflow blood nowadays. NghÄ©a LÄ©nh mountain- 175m high like head of a dragon direct to the South and the body of this dragon are Trá»�c mountain, Váº·n mountain and Pheo mountain. NghÄ©a LÄ©nh mountain, Váº·n mountain and Trá»�c mountain\'s regarded as \"Tam SÆ¡n Cáº¥m Ä�á»‹a\" (3 forbidden mountain).</p>','Wikipedia','','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_square.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_thumbnail.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_small.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_crop.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_medium.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_large.jpg','active',3,'2010-08-31 16:27:03',1,'admin','2010-08-31 16:30:03',1,'admin',1,'admin','2010-08-31 16:27:10',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'en_US'),(28,21,'Lá»… há»™i Ä‘á»�n HÃ¹ng','','le-hoi-den-hung','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">H&ugrave;ng temple, locating in NghÄ©a LÄ©nh mountain, Cá»• T&iacute;ch village, Hy CÆ°Æ¡ng commune, Phong Ch&acirc;u district, Ph&uacute; Thá»� province, is the most sacred Vietnamese national historic and cultural complex site.</p>','<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D&ugrave; ai Ä‘i ngÆ°á»£c vá»� xu&ocirc;i<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nhá»› ng&agrave;y giá»— tá»• m&ugrave;ng mÆ°á»�i th&aacute;ng ba<br /><br />Lá»… há»™i Ä‘á»�n H&ugrave;ng c&ograve;n gá»�i l&agrave; Giá»— tá»• H&ugrave;ng VÆ°Æ¡ng l&agrave; má»™t lá»… há»™i lá»›n mang táº§m v&oacute;c quá»‘c gia á»Ÿ Viá»‡t Nam, tÆ°á»Ÿng nhá»›