oup.<br /><br />When made in style of a hot pot, canh chua is called láº©u canh chua.</p>','Wikipedia','','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_square.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_thumbnail.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_small.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_crop.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_medium.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_large.jpg','active',1,'2010-08-31 17:33:55',1,'admin',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'admin','2010-08-31 17:34:04',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'en_US'),(34,17,'Canh chua','','canh-chua','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Canh chua l&agrave; t&ecirc;n gá»�i cá»§a nhá»¯ng m&oacute;n Äƒn nhiá»�u nÆ°á»›c v&agrave; c&oacute; vá»‹ chua do Ä‘Æ°á»£c náº¥u báº±ng c&aacute;c nguy&ecirc;n liá»‡u phá»‘i trá»™n vá»›i gia vá»‹ táº¡o chua.</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd9c2e4dfa_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Má»™t b&aacute;t <em>canh chua</em></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Canh chua thÆ°á»�ng Ä‘Æ°á»£c d&ugrave;ng á»Ÿ nhá»¯ng v&ugrave;ng n&oacute;ng nhÆ° miá»�n Nam, miá»�n Trung, hoáº·c nhá»¯ng l&uacute;c n&oacute;ng ná»±c cá»§a m&ugrave;a h&egrave; miá»�n Báº¯c Viá»‡t Nam, m&oacute;n canh chua n&agrave;y cÅ©ng Ä‘áº·c biá»‡t phá»• biáº¿n trong nghá»‡ thuáº­t áº©m thá»±c H&agrave; Ná»™i.<br /><br />Nguy&ecirc;n liá»‡u ch&iacute;nh Ä‘á»ƒ náº¥u canh chua l&agrave; loáº¡i rau cá»§ quáº£, c&aacute;c loáº¡i thá»‹t hay thá»§y sáº£n (c&aacute;, t&ocirc;m, cua, á»‘c, háº¿n, trai, s&ograve;) kh&aacute;c nhau, trong Ä‘&oacute; thÆ°á»�ng d&ugrave;ng má»™t loáº¡i rau chua hoáº·c má»™t gia vá»‹ chua Ä‘á»ƒ táº¡o vá»‹ chua thÆ¡m ngon cho nÆ°á»›c canh. Ráº¥t phá»• biáº¿n c&aacute;c m&oacute;n canh chua sá»­ dá»¥ng nguy&ecirc;n liá»‡u ch&iacute;nh l&agrave; má»™t loáº¡i thá»§y sáº£n, háº£i sáº£n, do cháº¥t táº¡o chua c&oacute; t&aacute;c dá»¥ng khá»­ m&ugrave;i vá»‹ tanh cá»§a nguy&ecirc;n liá»‡u n&agrave;y. CÅ©ng kh&ocirc;ng hiáº¿m khi canh chua chá»‰ l&agrave; má»™t b&aacute;t nÆ°á»›c luá»™c rau cho th&ecirc;m ch&uacute;t nÆ°á»›c cá»‘t chanh, ch&uacute;t l&aacute; me hay v&agrave;i quáº£ sáº¥u xanh.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Ä�áº·c Ä‘iá»ƒm</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Má»™t Ä‘áº·c Ä‘iá»ƒm ráº¥t quan trá»�ng Ä‘&atilde; Ä‘Æ°á»£c d&acirc;n gian Ä‘&uacute;c káº¿t bao Ä‘á»�i l&agrave; Ä‘á»ƒ náº¥u ngon c&aacute;c m&oacute;n canh chua, t&ugrave;y theo nguy&ecirc;n liá»‡u ch&iacute;nh l&agrave; g&igrave;, sáº½ Ä‘Æ°á»£c sá»­ dá»¥ng cháº¥t táº¡o chua v&agrave; liá»�u lÆ°á»£ng chua kh&aacute;c nhau. C&aacute;c loáº¡i canh c&aacute; náº¥u chua kh&ocirc;ng bao giá»� d&ugrave;ng quáº£ sáº¥u hay chanh m&agrave; báº¯t buá»™c pháº£i d&ugrave;ng bá»—ng rÆ°á»£u, dá»�c, dá»©a v.v. NÆ°á»›c rau muá»‘ng luá»™c Ä‘á»ƒ nguá»™i váº¯t nÆ°á»›c cá»‘t chanh, hoáº·c cho quáº£ sáº¥u hay v&agrave;i l&aacute;t tai chua khi nÆ°á»›c c&ograve;n n&oacute;ng. Canh ri&ecirc;u cua náº¥u dáº¥m bá»—ng hoáº·c quáº£ dá»�c nÆ°á»›ng ch&iacute;n b&oacute;c vá»�. Canh ri&ecirc;u háº¿n, trai, tr&ugrave;ng trá»¥c pháº£i náº¥u vá»›i me. Sá»± phá»‘i trá»™n gia vá»‹ táº¡o chua v&agrave; nguy&ecirc;n liá»‡u ch&iacute;nh c&oacute; thá»ƒ linh Ä‘á»™ng, thÆ°á»�ng dá»±a tr&ecirc;n kinh nghiá»‡m áº©m thá»±c cá»§a ngÆ°á»�i ná»™i trá»£.<br /><br />Th&ecirc;m v&agrave;o Ä‘&oacute;, c&aacute;c loáº¡i rau gia vá»‹ (nhÆ° h&agrave;nh, th&igrave; l&agrave;, l&aacute; gáº¥c, rau rÄƒm v.v.) Ä‘Æ°á»£c gia v&agrave;o m&oacute;n canh chua pháº£i t&ugrave;y theo loáº¡i, nhÆ° canh ri&ecirc;u cua kh&ocirc;ng thá»ƒ thiáº¿u h&agrave;nh, canh c&aacute; náº¥u chua pháº£i d&ugrave;ng th&igrave; l&agrave;, canh háº¿n d&ugrave;ng rau rÄƒm v.v. C&aacute;c loáº¡i rau gia vá»‹ kh&ocirc;ng Ä‘Æ°á»£c gia v&agrave;o ná»“i canh trong l&uacute;c náº¥u, tháº­m ch&iacute; kh&ocirc;ng n&ecirc;n Ä‘á»ƒ dÆ°á»›i Ä‘&aacute;y b&aacute;t m&uacute;c canh l&ecirc;n v&igrave; dÆ°á»›i t&aacute;c dá»¥ng cá»§a vá»‹ chua rau sáº½ v&agrave;ng, tr&ocirc;ng máº¥t ngon. ThÆ°á»�ng thÆ°á»�ng ngÆ°á»�i ta hay m&uacute;c canh ra b&aacute;t v&agrave; ráº¯c rau gia vá»‹ l&ecirc;n tr&ecirc;n.</p>','Wikipedia','','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_square.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_thumbnail.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_small.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_crop.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_medium.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cda8d94a50_large.jpg','active',1,'2010-08-31 17:38:36',1,'admin','2010-08-31 17:39:16',1,'admin',1,'admin','2010-08-31 17:38:55',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'vi_VN'),(35,2,'BÃ¡nh Ä‘Ãºc','','banh-duc','<p>B&aacute;nh Ä‘&uacute;c is a term used to refer to two different varieties of Vietnamese b&aacute;nh, or cake.</p>','<h2>Northern Vietnamese version</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In northern Vietnam, b&aacute;nh Ä‘&uacute;c is a cake made from either non-glutinous rice flour or corn flour. It is white in color and has a soft texture and mild flavour.photo It is typically garnished with savory ingredients such as ground pork, t&ocirc;m cháº¥y (grilled ground shrimp),photo fried onions, sesame seeds, salt, peanuts, lime juice, and soy sauce or fish sauce.photo Although it may be eaten on its own, it may also be served hot, accompanied by steamed meat or mushrooms.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cdd066d361_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>A bowl of northern Vietnamese b&aacute;nh Ä‘&uacute;c thá»‹t (b&aacute;nh Ä‘&uacute;c with ground pork and fish sauce)</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B&aacute;nh Ä‘&uacute;c is available at small stalls and is eaten throughout the day.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span id=\"Southern_Vietnamese_version\" class=\"mw-headline\">Southern Vietnamese version</span></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cdc71e1d42_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>A plate of southern Vietnamese b&aacute;nh Ä‘&uacute;c colored with Pandanus amaryllifolius leaf extract, and topped with sweetened coconut milk and sesame seeds</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In southern Vietnam, b&aacute;nh Ä‘&uacute;c is a dessert made from non-glutinous rice flour. It takes the form of gelatinous blocks that are often colored green by the addition of Pandanus amaryllifolius leaf extract. It is cooked by boiling the ingredients and allowing them to cool, solidifying into a jelly-like sheetphoto that is then cut into blocks.</p>','Wikipedia','','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cdc71e1d42_square.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cdc71e1d42_thumbnail.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cdc71e1d42_small.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cdc71e1d42_crop.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cdc71e1d42_medium.jpg','http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cdc71e1d42_large.jpg','active',3,'2010-08-31 17:45:30',1,'admin','2010-08-31 18:20:23',1,'admin',1,'admin','2010-08-31 17:45:37',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'en_US'),(36,17,'BÃ¡nh Ä‘Ãºc','','banh-duc','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B&aacute;nh Ä‘&uacute;c l&agrave; má»™t loáº¡i b&aacute;nh cá»§a Viá»‡t Nam, thÆ°á»�n