strict, Ph&uacute; Thá»� province, is the most sacred Vietnamese national historic and cultural complex site.</p>','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">H&ugrave;ng temple\'s the place of worship H&ugrave;ng VÆ°Æ¡ng- the first King of Vietnam and the first son of Láº¡c Long Qu&acirc;n and &Acirc;u CÆ¡. H&ugrave;ng temple\'s also the place where was the center of the first capital of Vietnam- Phong Ch&acirc;u, according to ancient tales. It is the symbol of glorious Ä�&ocirc;ng SÆ¡n culture. This temple is the most significant political and social institution of Vietnam. For thousands of year, all Vietnamese dynasties and governments have always regarded it as \"Nam Viá»‡t Triá»‡u Tá»•\" (place of Vietnamese millionth-generation ancestor). All Vietnamese people are proud of it and remember to celebrate Giá»— Tá»• H&ugrave;ng VÆ°Æ¡ng every 10th day of 3rd lunar month here.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Locating</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It told that once upon a time, H&ugrave;ng VÆ°Æ¡ng The First was looking for a place to set up the capital. The King had gone to 99 places but he hadn\'t been satisfactory. One day, he gone to Hy CÆ°Æ¡ng village. Immediately, his horse whinny resoundingly. He stopped and gone to the highest mountain- NghÄ©a LÄ©nh, saw four directions. At last, he decided to choose this place.<br /><br />Ph&uacute; Thá»� is fat and green midland area. In Fengshui opinion, Phong Ch&acirc;u is the land of \"sÆ¡n cháº§u thá»§y tá»¥\" (place where mountains and rivers gather), \"long cháº§u há»• phá»¥c\" (place where dragons and tigers attend upon), \"phÆ°á»£ng bay ngá»±a cháº¡y\" (place where phoenixes fly and horses run) and the land where\'s abundant in \"kh&iacute; thi&ecirc;ng s&ocirc;ng n&uacute;i\" (sacred country\'s qi- flow of energy). This place is full of obstacles and difficult of access that\'s easy to protect, but also easy of access to welcome people come from other places. This is the confluence of 3